(2, 14, 2, '7', 'Bahçelievler', 'bahcelievler', 'bahcelievler-2023-03-23-641c5888b0e5e.jpg', '<p>Located on the European side of Istanbul, Bah&ccedil;elievler is a peaceful suburb known for its green spaces and family-friendly atmosphere. Its name translates to \"houses with gardens\" in Turkish, and the area lives up to this description with its leafy streets and well-tended parks. Come on, allow us to take you on a journey in this beautiful suburb and discuss the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bah&ccedil;elievler History</li>\r\n<li>Bah&ccedil;elievler Culture</li>\r\n<li>Bah&ccedil;elievler Location</li>\r\n<li>Bah&ccedil;elievler Neighbourhoods</li>\r\n<li>Bah&ccedil;elievler Real Estate</li>\r\n<li>Bah&ccedil;elievler Transportation</li>\r\n<li>Bah&ccedil;elievler Health Care</li>\r\n<li>Bah&ccedil;elievler Education</li>\r\n<li>Bah&ccedil;elievler Entertainment and Tourist Attractions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Bah&ccedil;elievler History</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Bah&ccedil;elievler was founded in the early 20th century, as Istanbul began to expand beyond its old city walls. The area was originally home to a few wealthy families who built summer homes here, but over time it grew into a more diverse community.</p>\r\n<p>Today, Bah&ccedil;elievler is home to a mix of middle-class and upper-middle-class residents, many of whom work in nearby areas such as Bakırk&ouml;y or G&uuml;neşli.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>Bah&ccedil;elievler Culture</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Bah&ccedil;elievler is known for its rich cultural heritage and diverse community. The neighbourhood is home to several historical sites, including the Kocasinan Cultural Centre and the Atak&ouml;y A Plus Exhibition Centre, which host a range of cultural events and exhibitions throughout the year. Additionally, Bah&ccedil;elievler has a vibrant arts scene, with several galleries and theatres showcasing the work of local artists and performers. The neighbourhood also has a rich cul